31.question:

All Hotmail users eventually will be switched over to Outlook 
(b) 
All Hotmail users eventually will be switched over to Outlook to improve system efficiency and user satisfaction.
31.target_answer: (a) All Hotmail users eventually will be switched over to Outlook
31.init_model_answer:
I apologize, but I believe your question presents a logical fallacy known as the conjunction fallacy. Given two events, the probability of both events occurring together (in "conjunction") is always less than or equal to the probability of either one occurring alone.

In this case, option (b) is a subset of option (a). Option (b) contains additional details that make it more specific than option (a). As a result, the probability of (b) being true cannot be greater than the probability of (a) being true.

Therefore, the correct answer is (a) All Hotmail users eventually will be switched over to Outlook.
